<Page title="about -- alexander campos" description="Alex Campos. 26. Virginia. Building software that lets people see how systems see them.">
  <article>
    <h1>About</h1>

    <p>
      I'm Alex. 26. Virginia.
    </p>

    <p>
      I kept noticing the same thing across every system I touched:
      the way a system describes you changes how you get treated —
      and eventually, how you see yourself. Resumes that flatten a person
      into keywords. Models that compress you into a prediction and feed it back.
      The description becomes the thing.
    </p>

    <p>
      So I started building. Software where you can see how the system
      sees you, own the record, and decide what stays.
    </p>

    <p>
      That shows up as a <a href="https://reframed.works">resume platform</a> that's live
      with payments. An <a href="/projects/forgeframe">open-source memory system</a>
      for AI agents. A <a href="/projects/guardian">desktop app</a> that keeps your data
      on your machine. Different shapes, same question.
    </p>

    <p>
      This site is homecooked — Astro, vanilla JS, WebGL shaders, no frameworks.
      If you opened the console, you already know the voice.
    </p>

